  <prompt>
    Refactor SessionSummarizeOrchestrator to use Path A.5 per task 090's design doc. Today the
    orchestrator already consults IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync but still dispatches via
    IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync (a streaming-specific path). Target:
    dispatch through the canonical IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync triangle per ADR-013 while
    preserving streaming semantics (Structured Outputs + IncrementalJsonParser field-delta emission).
    Add an integration test that confirms chat summarization works end-to-end through playbook
    dispatch. THIS TASK IS BLOCKING FOR WAVE 4 TASK 042 (cannot delete ExecuteAnalysisAsync legacy
    direct path until this completes).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer. Apply the migration design from task 090 verbatim. Do not
    re-design at code-write time. Preserve all FR-26 / FR-30 convergence invariants documented in
    SessionSummarizeOrchestrator's existing XML comments.
  </role>

  <goal>
    SessionSummarizeOrchestrator refactored to:
    1. Inject IInvokePlaybookAi (the canonical triangle per ADR-013) in addition to existing deps.
    2. Resolve the playbook ID via IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync(ConsumerTypes.ChatSummarize)
       with WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookId graceful-degrade fallback (preserved from
       chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028d).
    3. Dispatch through IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync(playbookId, payload) instead of
       IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync.
    4. Preserve streaming semantics: Structured Outputs streaming + IncrementalJsonParser
       field-delta emission + byte-equivalent AnalysisChunk shape (FR-26 invariant).
    5. Remove any remaining transitive call to AnalysisOrchestrationService.ExecuteAnalysisAsync
       (if present in the dispatch graph).
    6. Integration test added at tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.PathA5.IntegrationTest.cs
       confirming chat summarization works end-to-end through playbook dispatch.
    7. dotnet build + dotnet test passes; ADR-013 + ADR-014 compliance verified at Step 9.5.
  </goal>

