  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — re-inject IConsumerRoutingService + IInvokePlaybookAi (both already DI-registered). No new abstraction layers. No new interfaces beyond what already exists.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — IInvokePlaybookAi triangle is canonical. Dispatch MUST route through this surface, NOT through IPlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteChatSummarizeAsync. SessionSummarizeOrchestrator becomes a thin chat-session boundary that forwards to the canonical triangle.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Caching — IConsumerRoutingService 5-min TTL is preserved verbatim. No new invalidation logic (NFR-04 explicitly out of R7 scope).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — verify publish-size delta at end of task (expected: minimal change since IInvokePlaybookAi is already registered; net code change is small refactor).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — integration test mocks IConsumerRoutingService + IInvokePlaybookAi at the boundary. Do NOT use Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt; (banned). No DI-registration tests, no ctor null-check tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17">Acceptance: chat-summarize consumer row in sprk_playbookconsumer table (task 092); SessionSummarizeOrchestrator uses Path A.5; integration test confirms chat summarization works end-to-end through playbook dispatch.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-04">Cache invalidation hook NOT in R7 scope — do NOT add new invalidation logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — load .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md before designing the addition. State placement decision: keep in BFF (chat orchestration is BFF-internal). Verify publish-size impact. Verify no new HIGH-severity CVE. Update corresponding tests (per Test update obligation §F).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification triple:
      1. Existing: SessionSummarizeOrchestrator + IConsumerRoutingService both exist; partial migration landed in chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028d.
      2. Extension: this task extends the existing orchestrator to complete the canonical-triangle migration. NO new component introduced.
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: ExecuteAnalysisAsync legacy direct path cannot be deleted in Wave 4 task 042; ADR-013 canonical-triangle invariant remains violated; chat-summarize stays on a streaming-specific dispatch surface that is incompatible with the R7 "every consumer dispatches a real playbook" uniformity goal.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist applies. Placement decision: KEEP IN BFF — SessionSummarizeOrchestrator is the chat-session boundary; this task only re-wires dispatch, does not move the orchestrator. No facade change. No public-contract change.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test update obligation — PR modifying Services/Ai/Chat/ MUST add/update tests in tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/. Integration test added per goal item 6.</constraint>
  </constraints>

